freeglut: FreeGLUT (A free OpenGL utility toolkit)
freeglut:
freeglut: freeglut is a completely OpenSourced alternative to the OpenGL
freeglut: Utility Toolkit (GLUT) library.  GLUT was originally written by
freeglut: Mark Kilgard to support the sample programs in the second edition
freeglut: OpenGL 'RedBook'.  Since then, GLUT has been used in a wide variety
freeglut: of practical applications because it is simple, widely available
freeglut: and highly portable.
freeglut: GLUT (and hence freeglut) allows the user to create and manage
freeglut: windows containing OpenGL contexts on a wide range of platforms and
freeglut: also read the mouse, keyboard and joystick functions.
freeglut: freeglut is released under the X-Consortium license.
freeglut: Packaged by Georgi D. Sotirov <gdsotirov@gmail.com>
